</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="73EB65373123FFB8B6A7F9BFFCCAF9FF" box="[151,786,1626,1651]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378" type="description">
<paragraph id="3B4E36BC3123FFB8B6A7F9BFFCCAF9FF" blockId="3.[151,1437,1626,1975]" box="[151,786,1626,1651]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3123FFB8B6A7F9BFFEF5F9FF" bold="true" box="[151,301,1626,1651]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Total length.</emphasis>
Male holotype 11.0 mm; female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="73EB65373123FFB8B6F7F99BFDFEF83B" pageId="3" pageNumber="378" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="3B4E36BC3123FFB8B6F7F99BFEBAF953" blockId="3.[151,1437,1626,1975]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3123FFB8B6F7F99BFD7AF91B" bold="true" box="[199,674,1662,1687]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">
<typeStatus id="E44A881E3123FFB8B6F7F99BFEECF91B" box="[199,308,1662,1687]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Holotype</typeStatus>
description. Head and thorax.
</emphasis>
Structural features of head and thorax much as described above for 
<taxonomicName id="FCF14D3F3123FFB8B6A7F946FEDDF937" authority="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,261,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3123FFB8B6A7F946FEDDF937" box="[151,261,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">A. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="12B657D53123FFB8B73CF947FEBFF937" box="[268,359,1698,1723]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3123FFB8B73CF947FEBFF937" bold="true" box="[268,359,1698,1723]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, except median length of crown slightly greater than interocular width and approximately 8/10 transocular width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B4E36BC3123FFB8B6F7F90FFDFEF83B" blockId="3.[151,1437,1626,1975]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3123FFB8B6F7F90FFEC8F88F" bold="true" box="[199,272,1770,1795]" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Color.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393123FFB8B7D6F90FFDE2F88F" box="[486,570,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) mostly dark green with inconspicuous yellow or brown markings; apex of crown with yellow macula bordered by pair of brown maculae; lateral margins of crown brownish-yellow with dark brown to black lines associated with muscle impressions; coronal, frontogenal, and temporal sutures dark brown to black; mesonotum with pair of basal yellow maculae. Forewing (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393123FFB8B5D3F8B3FBB0F8E3" box="[995,1128,1878,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Figs. 10–11</figureCitation>
) mostly dark green, except apical membranous area. Face and lateral and ventral portions of thorax (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393123FFB8B5E6F89FFBFFF81F" box="[982,1063,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) mostly yellow; labium, labrum, and legs (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393123FFB8B733F87BFE8AF83B" box="[259,338,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="378">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) brownish-yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="6F8E66343124FFBFB6A7FAA5FADAFA3F" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" targetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="3B4E36BC3124FFBFB6A7FAA5FADAFA3F" blockId="4.[151,1436,1344,1459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3124FFBFB6A7FAA5FE8DFADA" bold="true" box="[151,341,1344,1367]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">FIGURES 10–18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FCF14D3F3124FFBFB76DFAA7FDDAFADB" authority="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[349,514,1345,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felixi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3124FFBFB76DFAA7FDDAFADB" box="[349,514,1345,1367]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Acrogonia felixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="12B657D53124FFBFB43AFAA4FD84FADA" box="[522,604,1345,1366]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3124FFBFB43AFAA4FD84FADA" bold="true" box="[522,604,1345,1366]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 1 4, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="73EB65373124FFBFB6F7FA3FFE48F8F3" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" type="description">
<paragraph id="3B4E36BC3124FFBFB6F7FA3FFF2DF8D7" blockId="4.[151,1437,1498,2027]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3124FFBFB6F7FA3FFEA4FA7F" bold="true" box="[199,380,1498,1523]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393124FFBFB7C3FA3FFD92FA7F" box="[499,586,1498,1523]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, very strongly produced posteriorly; dorsoapical portion folded inwards. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393124FFBFB42CFA1BFDA9F99B" box="[540,625,1534,1559]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, with basal third broad, narrowing gradually towards slender median third; apical third digitiform, appearing articulated with median third; in lateral view, plate not extending as far posteriorly as pygofer apex. Connective (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393124FFBFB509F9A3FC56F9D3" box="[825,910,1606,1631]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, T-shaped but also expanded apically (and thus somewhat resembling an “I”); stalk narrow, without dorsal median keel; arms broad. Style (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393124FFBFB354F98FFF38F92B" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Figs. 14–15</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extending posteriorly farther than apex of connective; without preapical lobe, with slight median lobe; apical portion directed ventrally; apex acute (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393124FFBFB51CF957FC58F947" box="[812,896,1714,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393124FFBFB222F957FB41F947" box="[1042,1177,1714,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Figs. 16–17</figureCitation>
) symmetrical; shaft, in lateral view, elongate, gently curved dorsally, with pair of apical processes directed anterad (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393124FFBFB285F933FAD2F963" box="[1205,1290,1750,1775]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); dorsal area with process at anteapical portion and another one at apex, both dentiform (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393124FFBFB220F91FFBBFF89F" box="[1040,1127,1786,1811]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Anal tube (
<figureCitation id="A3CA2A393124FFBFB333F91FFA8FF89F" box="[1283,1367,1786,1811]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1344,1367]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,222,1296]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,193,1324]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Acrogonia felixi sp. nov. 10, body, male holotype (NCSU), dorsal view (total length 11.0 mm); 11, body, male holotype, lateral view; 12–18, male genitalia: 12, pygofer, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 14, styles and connective, dorsal view; 15, style, lateral view; 16, aedeagus, lateral view; 17, pair of apical processes of aedeagus, ventral view; 18, anal tube, lateral view.Scale bars:12 = 2 mm; 13, 18 = 1 mm; 14–16 = 0.5 mm; 17 = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) with distinct, median digitiform ventral process; basiventral portion with pair of small sclerotized projections directed to midline.
</paragraph>
