<subSubSection id="73EB65373124FFBFB6F7F86FFD28F867" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3B4E36BC3124FFBFB6F7F86FFD28F867" blockId="4.[151,1437,1498,2027]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3124FFBFB6F7F86FFE96F82F" bold="true" box="[199,334,1930,1955]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name, 
<taxonomicName id="FCF14D3F3124FFBFB4B8F86EFD18F82F" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[648,704,1931,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felixi">
<emphasis id="0985EAAE3124FFBFB4B8F86EFD18F82F" box="[648,704,1931,1955]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">felixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is given in honor of Dr. Márcio E. Felix (Laboratório de Biodiversidade Entomológica, Instituto Oswaldo Cruz, 
<collectingRegion id="F935F85E3124FFBFB526F84BFC18F84B" box="[790,960,1966,1991]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
) in recognition of his contribution to the development of Brazilian entomology and friendship.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
